          <div>Game Rules:</div>
          <ul>
            <li>Maximum 2 chances of throwing (girls have 3 chances). 
            </li><li>Catching team players can only catch with one hand (girls can use both their hands). 
            </li><li>The catcher should change with each throw. 
            </li><li>Team A - Attacking Team and Team B - Defending Team 
            </li><li>A destroys the pile of stones, A will try to rearrange the stones within 90 seconds. B will try to stop them from doing so by trying to hit players of team A below their Waist.
            </li><li>At a time, only one player of Team A is allowed in the inner circle for rearrangement of stones and maximum 3 players of Team B are allowed in the square but outside the circle.
            </li><li>Team B has to score out 2 players (3 in case of at least 1 girl in the team) to gain 2 points. If time runs out without arranging the stone, Team B gets 1 point. 
            </li><li>After rearrangement of stones, the player of Team A should shout ‘SATOLIYA’ loud and clear while tracing a circle around the pile then it gets 2 points. If a player of Team A shouts ‘SATOLIYA’ without completing the pile in any way, Team B scores one point. 
            </li><li>After three turns of each team, the team with more cumulative points will be declared the winner. 
            </li><li>In case of a tie, the winner will be decided by a bowl out (The team will be awarded a point if and only if they knock out at least one stone. The point will not be considered if the opponent catches the ball after hitting the stone).
            </li><li>Whole team is considered to be out if the opponent catches the ball that hits the stones (at least one stone should fall out) and the catching team gets 1 point. 
            </li><li>No players from defending team (Team B) is allowed to touch or make contact with any of the seven stones. (In case of any discrepancy, the Referee's decision will be final).
            </li><li>The players from team A are allowed to slide the stones on ground but must not throw them in the air although they are allowed to carry the stones with them while running.
            </li><li>Underarm throwing is not allowed. 
            </li><li>Breaking any of the rules will be counted as a foul. 
            </li><li>Referee's decision will be the final. 
          </li>  
          </ul>
